on every contemporary subject political, personal, and familial.Focusing on different stages of Drinker's personal development within the domestic context, this abridged edition highlights four critical phases of her life cycle: youth and courtship, wife and mother, middle age in years of crisis, and grandmother and family elder. There is little that escaped Elizabeth Drinker's quill, and her diary is a delight not only for the information it contains but also for the way in which she conveys her world across the centuries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aChildbirthzPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxHistoryx18th century. 0aChildbirthzPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxHistoryy18th century. 0aMedicinezPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxHistoryx18th century. 0aMedicinezPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxHistoryy18th century. 0aQuakerszPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxDiaries. 0aQuakerszPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxSocial life and customsx18th century. 0aQuakerszPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxSocial life and customsy18th century. 0aQuakerszSocial life and customs. 0aVaccinationzPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxHistoryx18th century. 0aVaccinationzPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxHistoryy18th century. 0aWomenzPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxDiaries. 0aWomenzPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxSocial life and customsx18th century. 0aWomenzSocial life and customs. 4aAutobiography. 7aHISTORY / United States / Revolutionary Period (1775-1800).2bisacsh  aAmerican History.  aAmerican Studies.  aAutobiography.  aBiography.  aGender Studies.  aWomen's Studies.1 aCrane, Elaine Forman, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package American Historyz978311041349608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package Complete